<subSubSection id="C338655BFFE3A624895611E626520B19" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8B9D36D0FFE3A624895611E6263E0A48" blockId="3.[106,286,505,529]" box="[106,286,505,529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<heading id="D0D581BCFFE3A624895611E6263E0A48" bold="true" box="[106,286,505,529]" fontSize="8" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" reason="4">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A624895611E6263E0A48" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[106,286,505,529]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624895611E6263E0A48" bold="true" box="[106,286,505,529]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Mimomys savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36D0FFE3A62489AC123926520B19" blockId="3.[106,745,549,2100]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A62489AC1239266C0A64" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[144,332,550,573]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62489AC1239266C0A64" box="[144,332,550,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Mimomys savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from Palaearctic Biharian sites. The Biharian biochronological unit is based on the co-occurrence of the genera 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A62488D9127925640A24" authorityName="Schrank" authorityYear="1798" box="[485,580,614,637]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62488D9127925640A24" box="[485,580,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Microtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248B45127925C10A24" box="[633,737,614,637]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248B45127925C10A24" box="[633,737,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Mimomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; it therefore extends from the first occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248BB5129825C80AC7" authorityName="Schrank" authorityYear="1798" box="[649,744,647,670]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248BB5129825C80AC7" box="[649,744,647,670]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Microtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(represented by 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624881A12B826990AE6" box="[294,441,679,703]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Allophaiomys</emphasis>
, which includes primitive members of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A624885312D726EE0A86" authorityName="Schrank" authorityYear="1798" box="[367,462,712,735]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624885312D726EE0A86" box="[367,462,712,735]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Microtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) to the disappearance of 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A624895612F727F20AA6" box="[106,210,744,767]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624895612F727F20AA6" box="[106,210,744,767]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Mimomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(represented by 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A62488AD12F726D90AA6" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[401,505,744,767]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62488AD12F726870AA6" box="[401,423,744,767]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624888512F726D90AA6" box="[441,505,744,767]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248B2812F725FD0B59" author="Fejfar, O. &amp; Heinrich, W. - D. &amp; Lindsay, E. H." box="[532,733,744,768]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="533 - 554" refId="ref13651" refString="Fejfar, O., Heinrich, W. - D., Lindsay, E. H. (1998): Updating the Neogene Rodent biochronology in Europe. - Mededelingen Nederlands Instituut voor Geowetenschappen TNO, 60: 533 - 554." type="journal article" year="1998">Fejfar et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248956131727DD0B79" box="[106,253,776,800]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Allophaiomys</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248813131626B20B79" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[303,402,777,800]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248813131626650B79" box="[303,325,777,800]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624886E131626B20B79" box="[338,402,777,800]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear roughly at the same time in Eurasia, around 2 Ma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C338655BFFE3A62489AC135525990C9F" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9D36D0FFE3A62489AC135525990C9F" blockId="3.[106,745,549,2100]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
In Europe, and more specifically in 
<collectingCountry id="F3357640FFE3A6248B071356254C0B38" box="[571,620,841,865]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248B42135525C80B38" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[638,744,842,865]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248B42135525B40B38" box="[638,660,842,865]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248B96135525C80B38" box="[682,744,842,865]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
characterises both the early Biharian (defined by the cooccurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A62489C71394267A0BFB" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[251,346,907,930]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62489C7139426310BFB" box="[251,273,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62488201394267A0BFB" box="[284,346,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A62488B5139426DB0BFB" box="[393,507,906,930]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62488B5139426BF0BFB" box="[393,415,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248896139526DB0BFB" box="[426,507,906,930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and correlated with the Calabrian Age, early Early Pleistocene) and the late Biharian (time interval when 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A624887713D326900BBA" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[331,432,972,995]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624887713D326410BBA" box="[331,353,972,995]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624884E13D326900BBA" box="[370,432,972,995]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248BF013D3279B0C5A" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248BF013D325C20BBA" box="[716,738,972,995]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624895613F4279B0C5A" box="[106,187,1003,1027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which corresponds approximately to the first part of the early Middle Pleistocene. Readers are kindly referred to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A62489BB143326410C1C" author="Gliozzi, E. &amp; Abbazzi, L. &amp; Argenti, P. &amp; Azzaroli, A. &amp; Caloi, L. &amp; Capasso Barbato, L. &amp; Di Stefano, G. &amp; Esu, D. &amp; Ficcarelli, G. &amp; Girotti, O. &amp; Kotsakis, T. &amp; Masini, F. &amp; Mazza, P. P. A. &amp; Mezzabotta, C. &amp; Palombo, M. R. &amp; Petronio, C. &amp; Rook, L. &amp; Sala, B. &amp; Sardella, R. &amp; Zanalda, E. &amp; Torre, D." box="[135,353,1068,1093]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="369 - 388" refId="ref13917" refString="Gliozzi, E., Abbazzi, L., Argenti, P., Azzaroli, A., Caloi, L., Capasso Barbato, L., Di Stefano, G., Esu, D., Ficcarelli, G., Girotti, O., Kotsakis, T., Masini, F., Mazza, P. P. A., Mezzabotta, C., Palombo, M. R., Petronio, C., Rook, L., Sala, B., Sardella, R., Zanalda, E., Torre, D. (1997): Biochronology of selected mammals, molluscs and ostracods from the middle Pliocene to the late Pleistocene in Italy. The state of the art. - Rivista Italiana di Paleontologia e Stratigrafia, 103: 369 - 388." type="journal article" year="1997">Gliozzi et al. (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248852143325490C1C" author="Masini, F. &amp; Sala, B." box="[366,617,1068,1093]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="43 - 56" refId="ref16194" refString="Masini, F., Sala, B. (2007): Large- and small-mammal distribution patterns and chronostratigraphic boundaries from the Late Pliocene to the Middle Pleistocene of the Italian peninsula. - Quaternary International, 160: 43 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. quaint. 2006.09.008" type="journal article" year="2007">Sala and Masini (2007)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248B9C1433262E0C3C" author="Masini, F. &amp; Sala, B." pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="43 - 56" refId="ref16194" refString="Masini, F., Sala, B. (2007): Large- and small-mammal distribution patterns and chronostratigraphic boundaries from the Late Pliocene to the Middle Pleistocene of the Italian peninsula. - Quaternary International, 160: 43 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. quaint. 2006.09.008" type="journal article" year="2007">Masini and Sala (2007)</bibRefCitation>
for correlations between Fejfar et al.’s (1998) standard biochronological scale based on small mammals and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248956149126010CFF" author="Azzaroli, A." box="[106,289,1166,1190]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="61 - 79" refId="ref12436" refString="Azzaroli, A. (1977): The Villafranchian stage in Italy and the Plio-Pleistocene boundary. - Giornale di Geologia, 41 (1 - 2): 61 - 79." type="journal article" year="1977">Azzaroli’s (1977)</bibRefCitation>
Italian Mammal Ages, on the one hand, and the International Chronostratigraphic Scale, on the other.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C338655BFFE3A62489AC14CF23680AED" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B9D36D0FFE3A62489AC14CF23B70908" blockId="3.[106,745,549,2100]" lastBlockId="3.[820,1459,151,692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A62489AC14CF261C0CBE" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[144,316,1232,1255]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62489AC14CF261C0CBE" box="[144,316,1232,1255]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Mimomys savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is first recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F3357640FFE3A6248B3314D0251F0CBE" box="[527,575,1231,1255]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Italy</collectingCountry>
based on a few remains from the localities Le Strette and Bosco Chiesa Nuova, in Upper Valdarno, where also large mammal remains of the Tasso Faunal Unit were found (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248B25152F25BE0D11" author="Bosco, C." box="[537,670,1328,1352]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="141 - 154" refId="ref12679" refString="Bosco, C. (1898): Hystrix etrusca n. sp. - Palaeontographia Italica, 4: 141 - 154." type="journal article" year="1898">Bosco 1898</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248B92152F25C50D11" author="Bosco, C." box="[686,741,1328,1352]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="85 - 104" refId="ref12703" refString="Bosco, C. (1899): I roditori Pliocenici del Valdarno superiore [Rodents in the Pliocene of the Upper Valdarno]. - Palaeontographia Italica, 5: 85 - 104. (in Italian)" type="journal article" year="1899">1899</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248956154E27FF0D30" author="Torre, D." box="[106,223,1361,1385]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="715 - 718" refId="ref17778" refString="Torre, D. (1985): Mimomys savini and Arvicola cantiana in the Upper Valdarno (Italy). - Eclogae Geologicae Helvetiae, 78 (3): 715 - 718." type="journal article" year="1985">Torre 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A62489D6154E26F20D30" author="Masini, F. &amp; Sala, B." box="[234,466,1361,1385]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="43 - 56" refId="ref16194" refString="Masini, F., Sala, B. (2007): Large- and small-mammal distribution patterns and chronostratigraphic boundaries from the Late Pliocene to the Middle Pleistocene of the Italian peninsula. - Quaternary International, 160: 43 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. quaint. 2006.09.008" type="journal article" year="2007">Sala and Masini 2007</bibRefCitation>
). These Lower Pleistocene deposits are magnetostratigraphically correlated with the base of the Calabrian Stage and biochronologically with the early part of the early Biharian; they therefore date to around 1.6–1.8 Ma (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A62489D115CC26BB0DB2" author="Torre, D. &amp; Albianelli, A. &amp; Bertini, A. &amp; Ficcarelli, G. &amp; Masini, F. &amp; Napoleone, G." box="[237,411,1491,1515]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="559 - 570" refId="ref17813" refString="Torre, D., Albianelli, A., Bertini, A., Ficcarelli, G., Masini, F., Napoleone, G. (1996): Paleomagnetic calibration of Plio-Pleistocene mammal localities in central Italy. - In: Nadachowski, A., Werdelin, L. (eds), Neogene and Quaternary Mammals of the Palaearctic. Papers in mammal palaeontology honoring Kazimierz Kowalski. Acta zoologica cracoviensia, 39 (1): 559 - 570." type="journal article" year="1996">Torre et al. 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A624889E15CC25190DB2" author="Azzaroli, A." box="[418,569,1491,1515]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="177 - 198" refId="ref12470" refString="Azzaroli, A. (1998): Hystrix etrusca Bosco, the late Villafranchian porcupine from the Upper Valdarno, central Italy. - Palaeontographia Italica, 85: 177 - 198." type="journal article" year="1998">Azzaroli 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248B7E15CC27810E52" author="Masini, F. &amp; Sala, B." pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="43 - 56" refId="ref16194" refString="Masini, F., Sala, B. (2007): Large- and small-mammal distribution patterns and chronostratigraphic boundaries from the Late Pliocene to the Middle Pleistocene of the Italian peninsula. - Quaternary International, 160: 43 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. quaint. 2006.09.008" type="journal article" year="2007">Masini and Sala 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A624898C15EC26860E52" author="Masini, F. &amp; Sala, B." box="[176,422,1523,1547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="43 - 56" refId="ref16194" refString="Masini, F., Sala, B. (2007): Large- and small-mammal distribution patterns and chronostratigraphic boundaries from the Late Pliocene to the Middle Pleistocene of the Italian peninsula. - Quaternary International, 160: 43 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. quaint. 2006.09.008" type="journal article" year="2007">Sala and Masini 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A624888A15EC27830E75" author="Rook, L. &amp; Martinez-Navarro, B." pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="134 - 144" refId="ref17030" refString="Rook, L., Martinez-Navarro, B. (2010): Villafranchian: The long story of a Plio-Pleistocene European large mammal biochronologic unit. - Quaternary International, 219: 134 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. quaint. 2010.01.007" type="journal article" year="2010">Rook and Martínez-Navarro 2010</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A624898E160B26F10E75" author="Breda, M. &amp; Marchetti, M." box="[178,465,1556,1580]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="61 - 77" refId="ref12742" refString="Breda, M., Marchetti, M. (2007): Pleistocene mammal faunas from the Leffe Basin (Bergamo, Northern Italy): Revision and new data. - In: Kahlke, R. - D., Maul, L. C., Mazza, P. P. A. (eds), Late Neogene and Quaternary biodiversity and evolution: Regional developments and interregional correlations, Volume II. Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg, 259: 61 - 77." type="journal article" year="2007">Breda and Marchetti (2007)</bibRefCitation>
correlated the 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248B55160B25C80E72" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[617,744,1556,1580]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248B55160B255F0E72" box="[617,639,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. cf. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248B96160B25C80E72" box="[682,744,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bearing levels of Leffe (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A624885C162B26C80E15" author="Stehlin, H. G." box="[352,488,1588,1612]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="648 - 681" refId="ref17627" refString="Stehlin, H. G. (1930): Die Saugetierfauna von Leffe. - Eclogae Geologicae Helvetiae, 23 (2): 648 - 681." type="journal article" year="1930">Stehlin 1930</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A62488CE162B258D0E15" author="Masini, F. &amp; Rook, L. &amp; Abbazzi, L. &amp; Ambrosetti, P. &amp; Azzaroli, A. &amp; Ficcarelli, G. &amp; Gentili, S. &amp; Kotsakis, T. &amp; Sala, B. &amp; Torre, D." box="[498,685,1588,1612]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="2" refId="ref16087" refString="Masini, F., Rook, L., Abbazzi, L., Ambrosetti, P., Azzaroli, A., Ficcarelli, G., Gentili, S., Kotsakis, T., Sala, B., Torre, D. (1996): Mammalian faunas of selected Villafranchian localities of Italy. - In: Carraro, F. (ed.), Revisione del Villafranchiano nell'area tipo di Villafranca d'Asti [The Villafranchian in the Villafranca d'Asti type-area: a revision]. Il Quaternario, 9 (1): pl. 2." type="journal article" year="1996">Masini et al. 1996</bibRefCitation>
) with the transition between the Early Pleistocene Tasso and Farneta Faunal units and therefore with the early Biharian. Scoppito (L’Aquila Basin) is yet another early Biharian site that yielded 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A624895616A826350E97" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[106,277,1719,1742]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624895616A826350E97" box="[106,277,1719,1742]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Mimomys savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A624881F16A926C60E97" author="Masini, F. &amp; Rook, L. &amp; Abbazzi, L. &amp; Ambrosetti, P. &amp; Azzaroli, A. &amp; Ficcarelli, G. &amp; Gentili, S. &amp; Kotsakis, T. &amp; Sala, B. &amp; Torre, D." box="[291,486,1718,1742]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="2" refId="ref16087" refString="Masini, F., Rook, L., Abbazzi, L., Ambrosetti, P., Azzaroli, A., Ficcarelli, G., Gentili, S., Kotsakis, T., Sala, B., Torre, D. (1996): Mammalian faunas of selected Villafranchian localities of Italy. - In: Carraro, F. (ed.), Revisione del Villafranchiano nell'area tipo di Villafranca d'Asti [The Villafranchian in the Villafranca d'Asti type-area: a revision]. Il Quaternario, 9 (1): pl. 2." type="journal article" year="1996">Masini et al. 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A62488CD16A925E70E97" author="Kotsakis, T. &amp; Abbazzi, L. &amp; Angelone, C. &amp; Argenti, P. &amp; Barisone, G. &amp; Fanfani, F. &amp; Marcolini, F. &amp; Masini, F." box="[497,711,1718,1742]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="313 - 342" refId="ref14732" refString="Kotsakis, T., Abbazzi, L., Angelone, C., Argenti, P., Barisone, G., Fanfani, F., Marcolini, F., Masini, F. (2003): Plio- - Pleistocene biogeography of Italian mainland micromammals. - Deinsea, 10: 313 - 342." type="journal article" year="2003">Kotsakis et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
). A younger age is assumed for the fossiliferous site of Soave/ Cava Sud (
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A62489E016E726860F56" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[220,422,1783,1807]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62489E016E726620F56" box="[220,322,1784,1807]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Mimomys</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A624885416E726860F56" box="[360,422,1784,1807]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A624888716E825090F56" author="Pasa, A." box="[443,553,1783,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 111" refId="ref16867" refString="Pasa, A. (1947): I Mammiferi di alcune antiche brecce Veronesi [The mammals of some ancient breccias from Verona]. - Memorie della Museo Civico Storio Nazionale di Verona, 1: 1 - 111. (in Italian)" type="journal article" year="1947">Pasa 1947</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248B0F16E825C50F56" author="Bartolomei, G." box="[563,741,1783,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="249 - 258" refId="ref12504" refString="Bartolomei, G. (1980): Micromammiferi del Plio-Pleistocene [Micromammals from the Plio-Pleistocene]. - In: Parisi, G. (ed.), Vertebrate Fosili italiani. Catalogo della Mostra. Commune di Verna, Verona, pp. 249 - 258. (in Italian)" type="book chapter" year="1980">Bartolomei 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248956170826530F69" author="Masini, F. &amp; Santini, G." box="[106,371,1815,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="355 - 380" refId="ref16252" refString="Masini, F., Santini, G. (1991): Microtus (Allophaiomys) from Cava Pirro (Apricena, Gargano) and other Italian localities. - Bollettino della Societa Paleontologica Italiana, 30: 355 - 380." type="journal article" year="1991">Masini and Santini 1991</bibRefCitation>
), and further Italian early Biharian sites with 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A62489DF1726266B0F09" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[227,331,1849,1872]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62489DF172627D90F09" box="[227,249,1849,1872]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A62488311726266B0F09" box="[269,331,1849,1872]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are Monte Peglia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248B0C172727810F28" author="Van der Meulen, A. J." pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref17941" refString="Van der Meulen, A. J. (1973): Middle Pleistocene Smaller Mammals from the Monte Peglia (Orvieto, Italy) with Special Reference to the Phylogeny of Microtus (Arvicolidae, Rodentia). - Quaternaria, 17: 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1973">Van der Meulen 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A624898F174726AB0F28" author="Masini, F. &amp; Abbazzi, L. &amp; Lippi, P. &amp; Sala, B. &amp; Torre, D." box="[179,395,1880,1905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="78 - 90" refId="ref15745" refString="Masini, F., Abbazzi, L., Lippi, P., Sala, B., Torre, D. (1998): Review and new finds of Microtus (Allophaiomys) (Rodentia, Arvicolidae) from the Early Pleistocene of the Italian Peninsula. - Paludicola, 2 (1): 78 - 90." type="journal article" year="1998">Masini et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
), and Castagnone/Pontrestura I (Northern Monferrato, 
<collectingRegion id="49E6F832FFE3A624885C176626E70FC8" box="[352,455,1913,1937]" country="Italy" name="Piemonte" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Piedmont</collectingRegion>
, NW 
<collectingCountry id="F3357640FFE3A6248B34176625190FC8" box="[520,569,1913,1937]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Italy</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248B6C176627830FEB" author="Siori, M. S. &amp; Sala, B." pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="207 - 217" refId="ref17568" refString="Siori, M. S., Sala, B. (2007): The mammal fauna from the late Early Biharian site of Castagnone (Northern Monferrato, Piedmont, NW Italy). - Geobios, 40: 207 - 217. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. geobios. 2006.05.005" type="journal article" year="2007">Siori and Sala 2007</bibRefCitation>
). In the latter site fossils come from both the basal levels of the local sedimentary succession (1 
<superScript id="7C579B98FFE3A6248B7917A6256F0F9E" attach="left" box="[581,591,1977,1991]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">st</superScript>
Alluvial Unit, fluviatile deposits and soils) and from the Alluvial Unit, at the (pedogenetic) top of the sequence. At least the basal levels are late Early Pleistocene (late early Biharian) in age because 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248AB3108724D208F6" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[911,1010,152,175]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248AB31087248508F6" box="[911,933,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248A88108724D208F6" box="[948,1010,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
co-occurs with evolved representatives of 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248A0810A623180889" authority="" box="[820,1080,184,208]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Allophaiomys">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248A0810A624B10889" box="[820,913,185,208]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Microtus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248AA310A7230E0889" box="[927,1070,184,208]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Allophaiomys</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248D6110A623990889" box="[1117,1209,185,208]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">nutiensis</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248DF910A622A10889" box="[1221,1409,184,208]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248DF910A622A10889" box="[1221,1409,184,208]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Mimomys pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248A0810C6233908A9" box="[820,1049,216,240]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Ungaromys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248A0810C6248D08A9" box="[820,941,217,240]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Ungaromys</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248AE610C6233908A9" box="[986,1049,217,240]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">nanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248D1510C723D808A9" author="Giraudi, C. &amp; Mottura, A. &amp; Sala, B. &amp; Siori, M. S. &amp; Daniele, B." box="[1065,1272,216,240]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="517 - 526" refId="ref13838" refString="Giraudi, C., Mottura, A., Sala, B., Siori, M. S., Daniele, B. (2003): The Castagnone site (Cerrina Valley, Monferrato Hills, NW Italy): Early Pleistocene sedimentary record and biochronology. - Rivista Italiana di Paleontologiia e Stratigrafia, 109: 517 - 526. https: // doi. org / 10.13130 / 2039 - 4942 / 5520" type="journal article" year="2003">Giraudi et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248C3910C7244B0948" author="Masini, F. &amp; Sala, B." pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="43 - 56" refId="ref16194" refString="Masini, F., Sala, B. (2007): Large- and small-mammal distribution patterns and chronostratigraphic boundaries from the Late Pliocene to the Middle Pleistocene of the Italian peninsula. - Quaternary International, 160: 43 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. quaint. 2006.09.008" type="journal article" year="2007">Sala and Masini 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248A4A10E723690948" author="Siori, M. S. &amp; Sala, B." box="[886,1097,248,273]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="207 - 217" refId="ref17568" refString="Siori, M. S., Sala, B. (2007): The mammal fauna from the late Early Biharian site of Castagnone (Northern Monferrato, Piedmont, NW Italy). - Geobios, 40: 207 - 217. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. geobios. 2006.05.005" type="journal article" year="2007">Siori and Sala 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The fossil bearing stratigraphical sequence yielded a positive magnetization referred to the Jaramillo by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248A80112623B40908" author="Giraudi, C. &amp; Mottura, A. &amp; Sala, B. &amp; Siori, M. S. &amp; Daniele, B." box="[956,1172,313,337]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="517 - 526" refId="ref13838" refString="Giraudi, C., Mottura, A., Sala, B., Siori, M. S., Daniele, B. (2003): The Castagnone site (Cerrina Valley, Monferrato Hills, NW Italy): Early Pleistocene sedimentary record and biochronology. - Rivista Italiana di Paleontologiia e Stratigrafia, 109: 517 - 526. https: // doi. org / 10.13130 / 2039 - 4942 / 5520" type="journal article" year="2003">Giraudi et al. (2003)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36D0FFE3A6248A66114523680AED" blockId="3.[820,1459,151,692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
Late Biharian faunas with 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D53FFE3A6248D53114523F10928" authorityName="HINTON" authorityYear="1910" box="[1135,1233,346,369]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Mimomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savini">
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248D53114523A50928" box="[1135,1157,346,369]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC2FFE3A6248DAD114523F10928" box="[1169,1233,346,369]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">savini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found at Soave/ Monte Tenda (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248AF01165234F09CB" author="Bon, M. &amp; Piccoli, G. &amp; Sala, B." box="[972,1135,378,402]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="185 - 231" refId="ref12558" refString="Bon, M., Piccoli, G., Sala, B. (1991): I giacimenti quaternari di vertebrati fossili nell'Italia nord-orientale [The Quaternary localities of fossil vertebrates in northeastern Italy]. - Memorie di Scienze Geologiche, 43: 185 - 231. (in Italian)" type="journal article" year="1991">Bon et al. 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248D441165221809C8" author="Masini, F. &amp; Rook, L. &amp; Abbazzi, L. &amp; Ambrosetti, P. &amp; Azzaroli, A. &amp; Ficcarelli, G. &amp; Gentili, S. &amp; Kotsakis, T. &amp; Sala, B. &amp; Torre, D." box="[1144,1336,377,402]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="2" refId="ref16087" refString="Masini, F., Rook, L., Abbazzi, L., Ambrosetti, P., Azzaroli, A., Ficcarelli, G., Gentili, S., Kotsakis, T., Sala, B., Torre, D. (1996): Mammalian faunas of selected Villafranchian localities of Italy. - In: Carraro, F. (ed.), Revisione del Villafranchiano nell'area tipo di Villafranca d'Asti [The Villafranchian in the Villafranca d'Asti type-area: a revision]. Il Quaternario, 9 (1): pl. 2." type="journal article" year="1996">Masini et al. 1996</bibRefCitation>
), and Slivia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B21FFE3A6248A071185230B09EB" author="Ambrosetti, P. &amp; Bartolomei, G. &amp; De Giuli, C. &amp; Ficcarelli, G. &amp; Torre, D." box="[827,1067,410,434]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" pagination="207 - 220" refId="ref12360" refString="Ambrosetti, P., Bartolomei, G., De Giuli, C., Ficcarelli, G., Torre, D. (1979): La breccia ossifera di Slivia (Aurisina-Sistiana) nel Carso di Trieste [The bone breccia of Slivian (Aurisina-Sistiana) in karst of Trieste]. - Bolletino della Societa Paleontologica Italiana, 18 (2): 207 - 220. (in Italian)" type="journal article" year="1979">Ambrosetti et al. 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
